# Trivy Ignore File — CI Hardening
# Accepted findings are intentional design decisions for MVP.
# Review quarterly and remove suppressions as infrastructure matures.
# Last reviewed: 2026-05-18

# ALB must be internet-facing to serve public API traffic
aws-elb-alb-not-public

# ALB security group needs public ingress for HTTP traffic
aws-ec2-no-public-ingress-sgr

# ALB security group needs egress for health checks and upstream calls
aws-ec2-no-public-egress-sgr

# Public subnets require public IPs for ALB internet access
aws-ec2-no-public-ip-subnet

# ALB HTTP listener — no domain/ACM certificate provisioned yet for HTTPS
aws-elb-http-not-used

# Lambda X-Ray tracing — post-MVP observability enhancement
aws-lambda-enable-tracing

# DynamoDB encryption with AWS-managed keys is sufficient for MVP
aws-dynamodb-table-customer-key

# ECR encryption with AWS-managed keys is sufficient for MVP
aws-ecr-repository-customer-key

# CloudWatch log group CMK — post-MVP security enhancement
aws-cloudwatch-log-group-customer-key
